to run directly to the gold vault.

485
00:30:04,250 --> 00:30:06,958
Forty-five kilometers
of reinforced underground piping.

486
00:30:07,458 --> 00:30:08,291
Why?

487
00:30:08,375 --> 00:30:11,916
If anyone dares
to knock on this tiny door…

488
00:30:15,583 --> 00:30:18,875
the vault will flood
in less than 20 minutes, my friends.

489
00:30:19,625 --> 00:30:24,291
You might touch the gold, but you'll
get squished like a toad and drown.

490
00:30:24,375 --> 00:30:26,583
- It's incredible.
- (DENVER CHUCKLES)

491
00:30:27,833 --> 00:30:31,666
Everything is so difficult that
nobody expects anyone to try to break in.

492
00:30:34,166 --> 00:30:35,791
And that's why it'll work.

493
00:30:35,875 --> 00:30:37,250
In fact, it's very simple.

494
00:30:38,291 --> 00:30:39,833
If you apply a bit of talent

495
00:30:40,375 --> 00:30:41,208
and science.

496
00:30:41,291 --> 00:30:44,083
The best minds in engineering,

497
00:30:45,041 --> 00:30:46,208
in physics,

498
00:30:46,791 --> 00:30:49,916
in fluid mechanics…
Just picture them planning a heist.

499
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:51,375
Excellence in robbery.

500
00:30:51,916 --> 00:30:53,833
But how the fuck will you get in?

501
00:30:54,833 --> 00:30:55,666
Let's see.

502
00:30:55,750 --> 00:30:59,791
There's Civil Guard officers, security men
and the governor's personal escort.

503
00:30:59,875 --> 00:31:03,333
It's a strategic location.
The army will arrive in minutes.

504
00:31:03,958 --> 00:31:07,166
It is impossible to get in
dressed as a thief, of course.

505
00:31:07,250 --> 00:31:08,375
Now Sergio,

506
00:31:08,458 --> 00:31:12,166
imagine that you're the hero
the whole world is waiting for

507
00:31:12,250 --> 00:31:13,708
to save them from the chaos.

508
00:31:13,791 --> 00:31:16,250
(BOTH LAUGH)

509
00:31:16,333 --> 00:31:18,666
It's very easy
to create chaos, little brother.

510
00:31:18,750 --> 00:31:19,583
I'm telling you,

511
00:31:20,375 --> 00:31:22,250
they will receive us with open arms.

512
00:31:24,041 --> 00:31:26,708
CIVIL GUARD

513
00:31:27,208 --> 00:31:28,625
I'm Captain Garrido,

514
00:31:28,708 --> 00:31:31,083
first platoon, sixth BRIPAC company.

515
00:31:31,166 --> 00:31:32,291
Lieutenant Alcázar.

516
00:31:32,375 --> 00:31:34,750
My orders are to assume control
over security of the building.

517
00:31:34,833 --> 00:31:35,750
Remove these people.

518
00:31:35,833 --> 00:31:37,833
(CROWD CLAMORING)

519
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:42,791
Enlarge the perimeter to 150 meters
from the front of the bank.

520
00:31:43,375 --> 00:31:45,875
And open the back door.
Convoy is on its way.

521
00:31:45,958 --> 00:31:47,958
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYS)

522
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:50,500
Girls, we're pulling up.

523
00:31:51,083 --> 00:31:54,958
We have orders to coordinate
with you… but not to let a convoy inside.

524
00:31:55,541 --> 00:31:56,875
Sir, the convoy's arrived.

525
00:31:58,333 --> 00:32:00,375
I will not give that order to my men.

526
00:32:06,250 --> 00:32:08,250
(CROWD CLAMORING)

527
00:32:10,916 --> 00:32:11,958
MAN: Stop the truck.

528
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:19,041
NAIROBI: <i>They're stopping us.</i>

529
00:32:21,416 --> 00:32:22,250
Sir.

530
00:32:22,708 --> 00:32:24,875
They require immediate access.

531
00:32:26,916 --> 00:32:27,750
Jiménez.

532
00:32:29,791 --> 00:32:30,958
Give me a radio.

533
00:32:36,041 --> 00:32:37,625
ALCÁZAR: <i>Defense staff headquarters.</i>

534
00:32:37,708 --> 00:32:40,458
This is Lieutenant Alcázar,
Civil Guard detachment.

535
00:32:41,791 --> 00:32:44,416
I need confirmation for access
of the BRIPAC platoon

536
00:32:44,500 --> 00:32:45,750
to enter the Bank of Spain.

537
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:49,375
What the fuck is happening?

538
00:32:54,416 --> 00:32:56,291
(PROFESSOR DISTORTED)
<i>This is Colonel Castro.</i>

539
00:32:56,375 --> 00:32:59,083
<i>We just declared alert level 5.</i>
<i>I repeat, alert level 5.</i>

540
00:32:59,166 --> 00:33:02,041
<i>From this moment on, the defense</i>
<i>of the interior of the Bank of Spain</i>

541
00:33:02,125 --> 00:33:04,250
and its perimeter is assigned to the army.

542
00:33:04,333 --> 00:33:06,833
You're to put all your men
under Captain Garrido's command

543
00:33:06,916 --> 00:33:09,208
until the arrival
of Colonel Cerceda, understand?

544
00:33:15,125 --> 00:33:16,750
Understood. Right away, Colonel.

545
00:33:18,541 --> 00:33:20,541
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)

546
00:33:35,875 --> 00:33:37,416
Push back the security perimeter!

547
00:33:38,041 --> 00:33:40,666
I want all that riffraff
on the other side of the street.

548
00:33:40,750 --> 00:33:42,750
(CROWD CLAMORS)

549
00:33:49,250 --> 00:33:52,000
Clear the area
until the full company arrives.

550
00:33:52,916 --> 00:33:54,375
Prepare the smoke canisters.

551
00:33:55,416 --> 00:33:57,416
ALCÁZAR: Prepare the smoke canisters!

552
00:33:57,500 --> 00:33:59,041
("HARLEN SHUFFLE"
BY BOB & EARL PLAYS)

553
00:33:59,125 --> 00:34:01,291
<i>♪ All right, good ♪</i>

554
00:34:03,625 --> 00:34:05,458
OFFICER: Authorization confirmed.

555
00:34:07,041 --> 00:34:09,333
<i>♪ You move it to the left ♪</i>

556
00:34:10,500 --> 00:34:12,333
<i>♪ And you go for yourself ♪</i>

557
00:34:13,125 --> 00:34:18,375
<i>♪ You move it to the right</i>
<i>If it takes all night ♪</i>

558
00:34:20,125 --> 00:34:22,208
<i>♪ Oh, come on baby ♪</i>

559
00:34:23,041 --> 00:34:25,625
Now we're in business. We are in.

560
00:34:25,708 --> 00:34:29,500
<i>♪ So you move to the left all night ♪</i>

561
00:34:34,500 --> 00:34:35,791
<i>♪ Come on, everybody ♪</i>

562
00:34:45,291 --> 00:34:48,333
- Have you ever heard of aikido?
- DENVER: I have, it's an air conditioner.

563
00:34:48,416 --> 00:34:51,291
It's those chocolate-covered sticks
that taste like cardboard

564
00:34:51,375 --> 00:34:52,833
that everybody eats but nobody likes.

565
00:34:52,916 --> 00:34:55,333
Aikido.

566
00:34:55,916 --> 00:34:57,916
Using the strength of your enemy
in your favor.

567
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,250
For instance, the ten of us cannot take
the Bank of Spain.

568
00:35:00,333 --> 00:35:03,708
The strength of our enemy is
far greater than our own. That's why…

569
00:35:05,875 --> 00:35:07,083
we will apply aikido.

570
00:35:07,166 --> 00:35:08,708
What do you mean, Professor?

571
00:35:09,291 --> 00:35:10,958
Whatever we can't do ourselves

572
00:35:11,458 --> 00:35:13,208
will be done by the Civil Guard,

573
00:35:13,833 --> 00:35:16,583
the Spanish Army
and even the bank's own security.

574
00:35:16,666 --> 00:35:17,583
(CROWD CLAMORS)

575
00:35:18,500 --> 00:35:21,583
PROFESSOR: <i>They will make sure</i>
<i>no one gets within 150 meters.</i>

576
00:35:22,791 --> 00:35:26,000
We will find out the exact number
of hostages in the building.

577
00:35:26,083 --> 00:35:27,916
How many people are in this building?

578
00:35:28,416 --> 00:35:31,333
The bank security guards
will give us the number.

579
00:35:31,416 --> 00:35:33,083
Three hundred sixty-seven.

580
00:35:33,625 --> 00:35:34,458
Aikido.

581
00:35:34,541 --> 00:35:37,541
I want all 367 down here in three minutes.

582
00:35:37,625 --> 00:35:40,208
PROFESSOR: We'll place charges
on the facade and windows

583
00:35:40,291 --> 00:35:42,000
in broad daylight without being seen.

584
00:35:42,083 --> 00:35:43,000
And how? (SNAPS)

585
00:35:43,083 --> 00:35:46,458
The smoke bombs the Civil Guard
will set off to disperse the crowd.

586
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:48,166
Aikido.

587
00:35:49,125 --> 00:35:50,416
(SHOTS)

588
00:35:50,500 --> 00:35:52,625
(CROWD SCREAMING)

589
00:35:53,500 --> 00:35:55,500
(ACTION MUSIC PLAYS)

590
00:36:23,791 --> 00:36:25,458
(VOICE OVER SPEAKERS) <i>Evacuation protocol…</i>

591
00:36:25,541 --> 00:36:28,625
PALERMO: I want everyone down here
in three minutes. Come on!

592
00:36:29,125 --> 00:36:31,000
- (OVER SPEAKERS) <i>This is not a drill.</i>
- Let's go.

593
00:36:31,083 --> 00:36:32,541
(OVER SPEAKERS)<i> Evacuation protocol.</i>

594
00:36:32,625 --> 00:36:36,625
We'll get the staff and customers
out by using perfectly-rehearsed protocol.

595
00:36:36,708 --> 00:36:37,541
And how?

596
00:36:37,625 --> 00:36:40,125
You heard it, we are evacuating.

597
00:36:40,208 --> 00:36:42,791
Everyone, gather in the hall right now!

598
00:36:46,166 --> 00:36:47,125
Come on, come on.

599
00:36:47,208 --> 00:36:48,625
OFFICER: Evacuation protocol.

600
00:36:48,708 --> 00:36:50,875
I want you to head out
in an orderly manner.

601
00:36:52,750 --> 00:36:56,500
PROFESSOR: <i>Civil Guard and security</i>
<i>will sweep the building, office by office,</i>

602
00:36:56,583 --> 00:36:58,875
and evacuate everyone
in less than three minutes.

603
00:36:58,958 --> 00:36:59,958
Aikido!

604
00:37:00,541 --> 00:37:01,791
STOCKHOLM: Hurry up! Hurry up!

605
00:37:01,875 --> 00:37:04,708
Hurry! Let's go, quickly!

606
00:37:04,791 --> 00:37:07,125
Come on, come on.

607
00:37:07,208 --> 00:37:09,541
That's it, keep going.

608
00:37:09,625 --> 00:37:12,750
They will help load in all the materials
we need for the heist.

609
00:37:30,625 --> 00:37:33,125
I'm going to ask you all
to please keep calm.

610
00:37:33,208 --> 00:37:37,166
We're going to evacuate the building
in two phases. Group one and group two.

611
00:37:37,250 --> 00:37:39,916
They will escort
all the extra hostages out of the building

612
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,958
and will have taken a problem
off our hands.

613
00:37:42,041 --> 00:37:43,250
ALL: Aikido!

614
00:37:43,333 --> 00:37:44,666
Group one, let's go!

615
00:37:44,750 --> 00:37:47,416
(CROWD SCREAMING AND CLAMORING)

616
00:37:49,833 --> 00:37:50,875
DENVER: Let's go!

617
00:37:50,958 --> 00:37:54,291
Let's go. All the way down,
all the way down! Go!

618
00:37:54,375 --> 00:37:55,958
(CROWD CLAMORING)

619
00:37:58,000 --> 00:37:59,583
Do not stop. Let's go!

620
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:04,458
I said do not stop!

621
00:38:04,541 --> 00:38:05,833
All the way! Go!

622
00:38:05,916 --> 00:38:07,125
Go, go!

623
00:38:20,208 --> 00:38:22,166
OFFICER: Move, move!

624
00:38:24,291 --> 00:38:26,875
And then,
when everyone is where they should be…

625
00:38:33,541 --> 00:38:35,125
we just have to press a button.

626
00:38:39,916 --> 00:38:40,958
And this button…

627
00:38:42,333 --> 00:38:44,041
<i>I'm the one who's gonna press it.</i>

628
00:38:45,750 --> 00:38:48,916
(BOMB BEEPING)

629
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:50,291
(BEEPING SPEED INCREASES)

630
00:38:54,416 --> 00:38:55,458
(BOMB BEEPS)

631
00:38:55,541 --> 00:38:56,666
(HOSTAGES SCREAM)

632
00:39:08,625 --> 00:39:10,625
(PANTS)

633
00:39:12,750 --> 00:39:13,958
No turning back now.

634
00:39:16,166 --> 00:39:20,166
("ASALTO AL CAMIÓN"
BY IVÁN M. LACÁMARA PLAYS)

